ing the apathy and arrogance of many of the teachers (NOT ALL – some were excellent instructors), the ****ers, the drugs, and the overall environment, I knew that these schools were neither a place for learning nor a place were kids could feel safe.  I know that there are some public school districts that are much better than the LA Unified Schools and I have no problem with those schools. Unfortunately, that is not the case in our area. Speaking of arrogance, how dare Benedikt call those of us who send our kids to private school “bad parents”? Who do  think YOU are to make such an asinine and ignorant statement? And to think that she gets to sound off on Slate… "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="978" language="en" documentId="2554" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="adgblue" date="Aug 29, 2013 8:53PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="2" thumbsDown="0" origId="2554" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="978"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>